args: All eyes turned to the sky that day.
No wind blew. No rains fell. But just as all hope\nfaded from the hearts of humans, a single blazing\nstar cut a brilliant streak across the sky.
It was a fascinating, indescribable color,\nsomehow black and white yet also neither.
But all who saw it spoke of it the same:\n＂It was a gentle, loving color.＂
Holy mana then rained down upon the land,\nand the people rejoiced in the knowledge they\nwould live in a blessed age, assured of prosperity.
The fiends are acting strangely...\nThere! An opening!
(And you're our best bud, so you better\ncome back to us in one piece!)
(Good. The Lambentree is restored.\nBut my mana is completely drained...)
(I've not even the strength to return to my\nphysical form in my own world.)
This mana flowing from the Lambentree...
I feel the prayers of everyone!\nDid the tree accept them and\nreturn them to me as mana?
(Then the Lambentree doesn't just pass the\nAuspex's mana on to the earth—it also\ntransforms prayers into NEW mana!)
(That explains why the mana\nis so dense here!)
With the mana I received from everyone,\nI can continue!
I can keep the chain of prayer unbroken!
An earthquake, miasma, and now a\nshooting star? I've read nothing like this\nin all the histories.
I fear the rite has failed...
Mind your words, Father; the Auspex will\nsucceed and return safely to us.
My faith in her remains unshaken.
The miasma is clearing...\nAnd that's not all!
This mana... It's not merely pure,\nit's also astoundingly powerful!
The rite is complete. Until this same day\nnine-and-ninety years hence, my mana\nwill keep this world safe.
Blessings and praise be upon her!
(I'M the blessed one; I've found something\nto protect and learned that I have the\npower to do so.)
(I will live here, in this world, until the\nday I'm able to fulfill my promise to you,\n{player_name}.)
And so, normal life continued from that day on.
But to me, everything felt brand new;\na sure sign that I, myself, had changed.
(Until recently, I even felt guilt in prayer.)
(I was certain a tainted creature like me\nwas unfit to offer up her prayers.)

(But knowing there are those in this world
who will accept me and permit my
presence here makes me able to offer
prayers once more.)
(I do so for the people I love as well as\nall who reside in this world. And—)
You really get into the zone when you\nmake with the prayin' these days, huh?
Y-yes, I suppose so! Perhaps it's because\nI'm not simply praying for myself anymore.
And also, because I must see these prayers\nto a destination beyond this world.
I'm sure they will find their way\nback to your world.
And I hold that belief in my heart as I\npress on in this kind and lovely world...
